text:
Overcooked, cardboard. The worst pizza and worst experience at a Pizza Hut. Told the manager that I  was disappointed. He told me that this cheese bites pizza that was overcooked so badly that the cheese had completely melted and burned out of the bites that were rock hard, was "perfect". That "nothing was wrong with the pizza" "if he made another it would look exactly the same" "you must not like cheese bites pizza because this is what it's supposed to look like" "you ate almost half off it and you touched the whole pizza" (a note on that last one: my family tried to choke it down before I took it back because it was awful. We ate 1 slice, 1 bite, and .5 slice)... as well as many other comments.
I had gone back to the store to have a satisfactory meal prepared, but given the manager's 'standard' of quality and attitude, I asked for a refund. To which he responded "That's what I figured you wanted all along", as if I would go through all this nonsense to somehow "get away" with one terrible slice of pizza. I expect better from this company, but if this manager is a representative of Pizza Hut, then there is definitely a customer service problem that people should be aware of.

text: First off customer service was terrible. text: If you like a good beer and a good burger, along with good service, we've found a place you shouldn't miss! There's a good positive vibe whether you want to sit inside or outside. Our server, Maddie, was a ball of positive energy and the perfect server; attentive but not annoying. We didn't have appetizers but the food came pretty quick. I ordered the Reuben with Grouper and there's a name for it but I forgot üôÉ. I was a little leary of eating blackened Grouper with sauerkraut but, it was Awesome! Jeff had a sandwich called the "Maddie B" which just happened to be named after our server üòâ. It's  a burger with 2 grilled cheese sandwiches as the buns. The burger was cooked to a perfect medium rare and he said he, "loved every bite". We will definitely be back!!

text:
We have come a few times and the service is always pretty consistent. Never bad, never amazing, but good.

The food is always what you would expect too. Well made, a few really good items (bang bang, the big pretzel when it is cooked right)

The nice thing is the 100+beers on tap and TVs all over.

The few items to know... the Pot Pie is massive...looking, it is about 10 inches wide but shallow. Which is a good thing because the crust rocks and the chicken is real.

The beer flights are nice ideas, but they are not labeled so you have to make a guess on what is what...

AND lastly... generally the wait staff has more tables than they can really handle so the service could be better.

Some servers are friendlier than others . The irish music is a lot of fun.

text: I ordered delivery. First off I would like to compliment the staff on their politeness, and professionalism. I had all of my condiments, he listened well to my precise directions. He is definitely in the right position for customer service. Michael was extremely kind, attentive, he showed that he cared for me as a customer in that moment. The driver was on time and my food was still hot. Red lobster, keep up the good work. You all made my Saturday night even better with the great meal. Thank you !

text:
Interesting place which seems to be like a Dinner, Pizza Parlor, Sandwich Shop. Called my order in and a nice person answered the phone like from Mel's Dinner. She was very nice and we had a quick short conversation because I had never ordered from there. I ordered a Chicago Beef Sandwich and Wings.
Arriving at the restaurant I found it very clean. It was a little dark inside but it had a nice atmosphere.
My food wasn't ready but the servers were on top of it.
Chicago Beef Sandwich was very tasty. Wasn't overly salty. And the juices to dip it into or very tasty. I thoroughly enjoyed it. The wings were very crispy and good as well.
I would be ordering from them again.

text:
Marcy, our Server, was great. Friendly, attentive & sweet. The wings were the best I've had in years! Bone in,, lightly battered were HUGE. Mild sauce was perfect, served with celery & carrots. Order of 10, I ate 3 they were so big & served right out of the fryer.
Steak fries were Marcy's suggestion...delish!! The boneless were just as tasty, as was the crispy salad...a mix of iceberg & spring mix, topped with all fresh veggies.
The restaurant was SPOTLESS, floors didn't have one crumb on them. And I looked! Manager on Duty visited every table. What a great dining experience.
Highly Recommend, family, friends & couples.

text: I've been many times and overall I like the place, but often leave disappointed in the service. For example, waiting 35 minutes for someone to greet our table and take our order is too long. Then when I asked a hostess if someone could assist us because no one has taken out order, I received a response of "well, someone was supposed to go to your table.". Why yes, I'm well aware that is what was supposed to happen.  Between the servers not being able to keep up with tables and the hostess being either unwilling to help or perhaps inept, I can't give this place a high rating. But I will give 3 stars for a descent burger, fries, and milkshake.

text: A cool "Friday Night Experience" with a live tribute band. Table reservation was done ahead of time online for $50 for a party of 6. Table reservation may not be necessary but the place becomes packed and I'm not sure if they allow standing room only. Arrive between 4-7 and you can enjoy a 2-4-1 Happy Hour Special. We ordered a variety of food with mix results. The $11.99 Friday Fish Special IMHO needs to have more Fish! Wings were good, so was Asian Lettuce Wrap and Flatbread. Shots at about $7 each were generous. Table service was a bit slow but somewhat understandable as it was very busy. The manager was friendly and quick to address our concerns. We sat away from the main stage which was nice to be able to enjoy the entertainment while still being able to have table take. They have live music everyday and Tribute Bands every Friday. We are definitely looking forward to going back!

text:
We stopped in there for lunch on a Tuesday.  It was pretty busy but we got our order in pretty quickly and was able to find a sit.  Overall, the place look clean, well decorated and had a certain vibe.  I think the bar with what looked like 8 or so drafts created a hang out like atmosphere. I was intrigued.

I ordered a bowl and a soft taco to see how things turn out.  The bowl was very tasty as was the soft taco.  I kinda liked them as an order.  However, there was just a little too much grease in the bowl.  My wifes taco was soaked in it as you can see from the pictures.

Also, things were not getting cleaned up very quickly leaving an unsightly mess at the trash cans.

So management, either upgrade your meat to eliminate the grease factor (maybe it adds to the flavor but soaking is not cool) or strain it off somehow and have someone pay attention to the trash, particularly when it is busy.  It cost you a star.

text: We were traveling to the Auto Train and wanted to have a nice lunch and a drink or two before boarding. My wife is legendary for her ability to pick great restaurants. Outdoor seating was a must, as important as good food. We have a habit of starting our travels with margaritas, despite the time of day. This was the start of our end, but we had their ultimate margaritas, which are like what I make at home. For lunch, we got 5 tacos: 3 coconut shrimp and 2 blackened mahi. We were quite pleased. The staff was nice too, friendly and attentive without being overbearing. Prices were fine. Recommended.

text: If you are looking for a true Puerto Rican style taste, don't waste your money here. Lechon had no true seasoning like back home (just salt), morcillas pre-fried put in a fridge and then are red-heated in the microwave, green bananas are cooked put in the fridge and red-heated in the microwave also very dry and tasteless. Arroz con gandules and even white rice ware uncooked. Is like, we couldn't eat anything on the plate and the only "discount" we got was for the got bananas with a total of $46 dollars. Tres leche was good tho (maybe because it's from a third party). The manager said "that's how it's supposed to be cooked", not in my country tho! All I'm saying is that, if you are looking for an authentic Puerto Rican lechon and food, don't bother!

text:
New review: We sat outside with our dog, had great service and delicious food. Thank you David for your service and for recommending the turkey dinner, it was just what I wanted. And my wife's stuffed pepper was big and yummy!

Previous review: My wife had the meatloaf dinner and I had the all you could eat fish. The food was as excellent as always. The service was not as good as usual. Their female servers are always wonderful but unfortunately we got a guy server who clearly is not cut out for the drive industry. He never once asked how our meals were, and in spite of being reminded twice that my wife's roll had not yet been provided, he never did bring it. And he never said anything about our empty glasses of water, so I had to stop him while he was attending to others. And when I did he brought me a glass of water but left my wife's empty one sit there. We'll be back because this is the only problem we've ever had and we love Our Place Dunedin, but we will request a different server if we get stuck with him.

text: I love Italian food!! This place had many things that I believe would be in Italy if I went. I really enjoyed the ambiance and the whole dining experience with my friends. The salad that I got to try with my friend was actually great as well as the meat and cheese platter. The risotto I had was pretty good and the pizza was good as well. I fell in love with their desserts. The tiramisu and mousse were amazing! They were light and would melt in your mouth. The flavors were awesome! All the ingredients used in the dishes were fresh and all of the food purchased was definitely homemade. The drinks were even good. I will also admit that their bathroom was one of the nicest bathrooms I have ever seen. It literally had everything. It was crazy! The service was quick and good as well. I would definitely go again and hopefully get their pasta next time.

I am visiting St Augustine but I don't think I'll be returning to this restaurant.

text: Was taking my husband out to dinner for his birthday. The big 50. He picked Sculley's from an online list of places near us. When we arrived we discovered the restaurant was not open. So he picked the restaurant located below as an alternative. When asked if we wanted outside or inside seating, we asked for inside seats. As such, we waited for a few minutes while the seating was prepared. Turns out it was way too hot outside to enjoy the "inside" setting, which was actually more of an open air patio style than inside (indoor) seating. I guess it was okay. The menu seemed to have more drink options than food options. Bird's kept landing on the tables and taking food. Not exactly my cup of tea. To each his own.

text:
First time for us eating at Fred's.  Is this place all hype or are the 4'100+ reviews right? I know when you see lots of benches and rocking chairs sitting around people like to eat here.

This absolutely is you local family friendly bring your out of town guests to kinda place. Eating here is an experience in its self. Omy goodness the staff is so friendly I felt like I made new friends. Seriously a buffet where you actually have someone really waiting on you like a genuine sit down meal. He explained the one plate, one of each and unlimited plates. Super cool concept for a buffet. There was no way we weren't trying multiple plates. Soooo many choices good luck trying everything. See pictures for what we tried.

This was like Eating at your family get together and all 50 of your family members brought your favorites. A place like this can bring a family together for a great meal. I will say Fred's Market is well deserving of no less then that 4.7star 4100+ reviews it has received.

text: I finally made it here! Honestly, I was avoiding it because it sounded hyped, but I am glad I went. It was AMAZING! I was quite skeptical, but they managed to impress me. Complimentary bread along with mac & cheese was good, but the dry-aged Swinging Tomahawk... OHHH, MAN! One of the best steaks I ever had, and I am a harsh critic because I live for good food. The flavor, the juiciness, cooked to perfection with a memorable presentation. Wow, I am hungry now. The potatoes were also beyond expectations! I am definitely coming back for more. Other than that, excellent service, and clean and pleasant atmosphere. Worth the money.

text:
I LOVE Sweet Tomatoes, it's my favourite place to eat.  *This branch is tired, it's not the cleanest and the furniture and carpet need upgrading.  Even so, I still love it.  They have delicious soups, and amazing salads.  Their muffins are delicious, my favourite being pumpkin spice which you get in fall. The blueberry is super delicious with white machine ice cream, sprinkles and caramel syrup!  I love it.  They do the most delicious strawberry lemonade, kinda sweet and sour at the same time.  The prices here are really excellent, particularly because you get coupons for discounts every week.  The price goes higher at 4pm and that is when they put out a 'special' dessert.  Always delicious.  Recommend!
*Edited to add. This place has been refurbished, It's lovely now.

text: I would give Cantina Laredo five stars for service and four for the food. We have eaten there twice and enjoyed both experiences. The chips and salsa are tasty- not too hot if that's your goal. They make your guacamole at your table and that is my favorite. Unfortunately the last time our entrees were not up to temp, but we ate them and they were better than most. The prices are very reasonable but my husband had a shrimp stuffed pepper for $18 and it only had 4 shrimp. Again the service was outstanding.

text:
The Good:
The restaurant had a lot of history within it's walls with Cuban memorabilia everywhere. It felt great sitting there amongst some history.  The drinks were good and the Red Bull Mojito was something new for me but it was a great risk that ended pleasant. My friends said they liked their drinks and one of them who has a palate for alcohol said the Cubra Libre was one of the best he has had ever.

The Bad:
I had the Cuban Sampler which was a mix of different meats and it was actually good. I wish their were more beans on my plate because they were DELICIOUS!! Out of the three meets I had the chicken was the best and that gravy was good but again, those beans were DELICIOUS and I felt shortchanged on the portion size.

The Ugly:
I think this place is a nice place to try Cuban food if you were interested in trying it.   I think the food and experience was great but if you want some good authentic Cuban food than you may want to do a little more research and try something that doesn't have a commercialized feel and setup.

Yours Truly,
Mr. The Good, The Bad, and The Ugly

text: My family (party of 11) met here for a nice dinner on the water. Unfortunately they would not allow us to sit outdoors, even though it was empty our entire visit and the weather was wonderful. Our server did a good job and everyone enjoyed their food. They took reservations, which was nice. A meal on average ranges $18-25. Cheapest option was a cheeseburger at $10 and most expensive was a seafood trio platter at $43. Each were present at our table and complimented. Everyone who ordered various seafood plates were pleased. I ordered a steak and it was cooked perfectly. My son had a grouper sandwich that was so soft you could tear it with your fingers.. he said it was delicious. The views from indoors were still enjoyable. One guest said Bloody Mary's were made great, however they are made in small scotch glasses. We would definitely return for a nice meal.

text: My husband & I originally planned to go to another seafood restaurant for dinner but they had a 2 hour wait. We decided to try RiverGrille on a whim. WOW am I so happy we did! We waited less than half an hour for a table on a busy Saturday night, leaving us time to take pictures in front of the beautiful outdoor scenery. When we were seated, the service and food were spot on. My crab-stuffed flounder was delicious and the gator bites were the freshest I've tasted. My hubby enjoyed the fresh catch of the day, which was swordfish. We don't live in the area but we will definitely be back for another outstanding date night during our next trip to Ormond Beach!

text:
We absolutely love food halls. We always look for them in cities that we travel to. When we found an all Asian one in Miami, we knew we had to try it.

Covid-19: they have an outdoor seating area that was pretty empty when we were there.

We tried B-Side, Yip, and Gold Marquess. Everything was fantastic. Our favorite thing was probably the sushi roll and crispy rice squares we got from B-Side.

Like many food halls, the down side is that this felt very pricey. It felt more expensive than more food halls.

I would absolutely recommend coming here while in Miami!

text:
Brandy, our server, was welcoming & attentive.
BF ordered combo w scallops, fish, mac n cheese & steak fries. The batter was light & seafood cooked perfectly. He did say the fries & mac were good, although mac was just warmed.
I had the stuffed flounder, collards & cheese grits. Flounder stuffing was rich (a bit less salt would've been perfect)& complemented the well seasoned fish.  Grits and greens were good.
Plates came w 2 hush puppies. Seemed like they had sugar in the mix so a little sweet.
Overall a good meal w decent portions, fairly priced. Nice atmosphere w hand etched glass panels.
We'll be back next time we're passing through.

text: Oh my goodness I cannot believe I never went to this place before! I guess that's what I get for judging it based on the fact that it's a barbecue place. I am totally a big fan now and you will be too!

text: This place is absolutely amazing! It's packed most of the time what we saw, the 3 days we were visiting St. Augustine. If you ever catch yourself around go and try it! The gentleman at the front of the line to greet guest and control the flow into the restaurant was fantastic. Very personable and funny. He was kind and courteous. He set the stage and we knew we were in for a treat. Walking in is beautiful with the string of lights in the trees. We were sat upstairs where you can view the water. It was a beautiful view. Now the food, was out of this world. I had the shrimp and grits while my fiance had the shrimp and chicken creole. It blew us away how good it was. Definitely our new favorite spot and now we're going to have to visit St. Augustine more often to visit this restaurant!

text: We have been meaning to check out this restaurant for a few years and finally made the trip. We thoroughly enjoyed every moment of the experience both visually and gastronomically. The outdoor deck is completely covered and offers panoramic views of the bay. Even on a warm day, the Gulf breeze was comfortably sufficient to keep the temperature pleasant. Our waiter was congenial and every one of his recommendations was spot on. The grouper, wolf fish, and salmon we had was excellent and the side dishes of red potatoes, grits, and coleslaw were as generous as they were tasty. The ambiance, great food, and spectacular desserts provided a wonderful milieu for us to catch up with old friends. I must add that their prices are quite reasonable especially considering we dined on fresh seafood. The only caveat I would offer is parking close to the restaurant can be challenging, but there is a shuttle that regularly makes the rounds from beachfront parking to all the shops and restaurants on Bridge Street.
